{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-recipe-page-js","path":"/rice-waffles/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Chez Nosredna"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"047d6de2-5b7a-519f-a3b3-18d519b543ce","excerpt":"If you make some extra rice for dinner the night before, then this comes together quickly.  If the rice is hot, be careful not to add the eggs directly to the…","html":"<p>If you make some extra rice for dinner the night before, then this comes together quickly. </p>\n<p>If the rice is hot, be careful not to add the eggs directly to the hot rice, or you risk cooking the eggs prematurely (in the mixing bowl). Better to first mix the dry ingredients, then whisk in the oil, milk, and eggs, and finally the rice. <em>Don’t forget the cardamom!</em></p>\n<p>These waffles don’t need any baking powder or other leavening.</p>\n<p>You can use a belgian waffle maker, but we prefer the texture that results from using a more traditional waffle iron (the thinner waffles have more surface area).</p>\n<h4> </h4>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 590px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/8b0ce5c3f5c55f98a2d17930d5d2e8d8/c4451/rice-waffles.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 131.75675675675674%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"original recipe\"\n        title=\"original recipe\"\n        src=\"/static/8b0ce5c3f5c55f98a2d17930d5d2e8d8/fcda8/rice-waffles.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/8b0ce5c3f5c55f98a2d17930d5d2e8d8/12f09/rice-waffles.png 148w,\n/static/8b0ce5c3f5c55f98a2d17930d5d2e8d8/e4a3f/rice-waffles.png 295w,\n/static/8b0ce5c3f5c55f98a2d17930d5d2e8d8/fcda8/rice-waffles.png 590w,\n/static/8b0ce5c3f5c55f98a2d17930d5d2e8d8/efc66/rice-waffles.png 885w,\n/static/8b0ce5c3f5c55f98a2d17930d5d2e8d8/c83ae/rice-waffles.png 1180w,\n/static/8b0ce5c3f5c55f98a2d17930d5d2e8d8/c4451/rice-waffles.png 1450w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Norwegian Rice Waffles","date":"December 26, 2020","description":"Carolyn Matthews' family recipe","prep":"20 mins","cook":"20 mins","servings":"makes five 8-inch waffles","tags":["Breakfast","Dessert","Vegan(ish)"],"tools":[{"name":"waffle iron","note":null},{"name":"whisk","note":null}],"ingredients":[{"ingredient":"⅓ cup sugar","note":"original calls for ½ cup"},{"ingredient":"1¼ cup flour","note":null},{"ingredient":"½-1 tsp ground cardamom","note":"original calls for 12 seeds (seeds, not pods)"},{"ingredient":"¼ cup vegetable oil","note":"original calls for half a stick of butter or margarine"},{"ingredient":"1 cup milk","note":"coconut milk is a delicious substitute, water is also fine"},{"ingredient":"3 medium eggs","note":"substituting flax eggs and/or chia seeds works surprisingly well"},{"ingredient":"3 cups cooked rice (1 cup dry)","note":"experiment with different kinds of rice!"}],"sauce":null,"suggestions":[{"ingredient":"butter","note":null},{"ingredient":"honey","note":null},{"ingredient":"jam or compote","note":null},{"ingredient":"maple syrup","note":null}],"full_img":{"publicURL":"/static/full-0cb51952dd25e838743e0162bb5841cc.jpg","childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1.3333333333333333,"src":"/static/0cb51952dd25e838743e0162bb5841cc/2f1b1/full.jpg","srcSet":"/static/0cb51952dd25e838743e0162bb5841cc/fd013/full.jpg 200w,\n/static/0cb51952dd25e838743e0162bb5841cc/25252/full.jpg 400w,\n/static/0cb51952dd25e838743e0162bb5841cc/2f1b1/full.jpg 800w,\n/static/0cb51952dd25e